OL,3,CArrears on household bills surge 25%
OL,4,Camong those in debt ` charity
OL,6,FCouncil tax arrears have increased by
OL,7,F14% in the last year to #1,972.
OL,9,FStepChange said fewer clients were now
OL,10,Fciting the cost of living as their
OL,11,Fmain reason for debt despite overall
OL,12,Fdebt levels rising significantly, and
OL,13,Fmany had struggled to rebuild
OL,14,Ffinancial stability after "years of
OL,15,Feconomic turmoil".
OL,17,FIn 2024, three in five clients (60%)
OL,18,Fwere in some form of employment, up
OL,19,Ffrom 59% and 56% in 2023 and 2022
OL,20,Frespectively.
